Package org.forgerock.openam.entitlement.utils.indextree.treenodes

Class RootNode

  • java.lang.Object
    • org.forgerock.openam.entitlement.utils.indextree.treenodes.BasicTreeNode
      • org.forgerock.openam.entitlement.utils.indextree.treenodes.RootNode
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    TreeNode
    public final class RootNode
extends BasicTreeNode
    Root node of the tree structure.

    As there can be many nodes at the root level, the idea of this root node was created to represent the parent of those potential nodes. This helps when describing algorithms by having a single point of access into the tree. It has no other function than to be an 'anchor' to the structure.

    Author:
    apforrest
